### Register (optional, only if you need a fresh user)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "me-test@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "name": "Me Tester"
}

### Login to get token
# @name login
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "me-test@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Get current user (/api/auth/me) - with valid token from login response
GET http://localhost:3000/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}

### Get current user - missing token (should return 401)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/auth/me

### Get current user - invalid token (should return 401)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer invalid.token.value
